Pre-setiger region relatively narrow, about twice as long as wide (
Fig. 15A
). Prostomium broadly triangular, narrowing to rounded tip (
Fig. 15A
); eyespots absent; nuchal organs not observed. Peristomium divided into two rings, first ring broadly rounded ending at narrower second ring bearing dorsal tentacles and first pair of branchiae (
Fig. 15A
); dorsal crest absent. Dorsal tentacles arising from anterior half of second peristomial ring, immediately followed by first pair of branchiae (
Fig. 15A
). Second pair of branchiae arising in a line posterior to the first branchiae dorsal to notosetae (
Fig. 15A
). Subsequent branchiae arising from similar location; branchiae not observed in middle and posterior segments.
